The Hawks in Durban have arrested two suspects for being in possession of drugs in Redfern, Phoenix on Thursday night. According to police reports, the officers had embarked on an operation after they received information regarding possible drug dealing in the area.The Hawks searched a house believed to be the premises of the drug dealing, and recovered 179 mandrax tablets, one piece of rock cocaine and dagga. Members also seized an amount of R14 700 suspected to be the proceeds of drug dealing as well as a licensed 9mm pistol with two magazines and 16 live rounds of ammunition, which were confiscated.The suspects, aged 22 and 52, are expected to appear in the Phoenix Magistrates Court today (Friday).